Why: the dec/enc close paths have the same SIGKILL leak shape as patch 0004 -
interruptible device locks plus early returns on firmware finish/timeout
failures skip the buffer frees, permanently leaking the instance's allocations
from the fixed pool (the fd is gone either way, so bailing out converts a
firmware hiccup into a leak). Locks made uninterruptible, buffers always freed,
VPU stop/reset ordered before the frees. Also disables decoder reordering
(reorder_enable=FALSE, the vendor's DEC_PIC configuration): the low-latency
no-B streams need no reorder delay.

